cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as it deals with the use of LiDAR sensors for perception and understanding of the environment by mobile robots and autonomous vehicles. The paper also proposes a novel deep neural network architecture for semantic labeling of LiDAR data, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses an automated process for data generation, which involves natural language processing techniques, and thus could also be relevant to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
